This paper deals with active learning, a subfield of machine learning, and specifically focuses on the scenario where the labeler can abstain from labeling or provide incorrect labels. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, since the paper primarily deals with machine learning and statistical analysis, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
